            <div class="content">
            <h2>Dear ITAN Author,</h2>
            <p>Welcome to <strong>ITAN Global Publishing (IGP)</strong>—we're thrilled to have you on board!</p>
            <p>Africa is home to incredible stories and gifted storytellers. Yet, for too long, African writers have
                been overlooked and underserved. We all published on platforms like Amazon KDP, only to be met with
                countless obstacles—unfavourable algorithms, royalty systems that shortchange creators, and platforms
                that weren't built with African writers in mind.</p>
            <p>A few indigenous publishing platforms emerged and shut down. They tried. But solving the complex puzzle
                of visibility and monetization for African literature requires more than just a sleek website and good
                intentions—it demands strategy, technology, and unwavering commitment.</p>
            <p>We marvel at how Publishing platforms in the West generate billions in book sales each year while we
                struggle. And the questions echoed in our minds:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>How do we make African stories profitable?</li>
                <li>How do we break the long-standing barriers that limit African literature?</li>
                <li>How do we take our stories beyond Africa's borders?</li>
                <li>How do we ensure African writers are seen, heard, and paid?</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Over time, answers began to surface—through breakthrough ideas, modern technologies, and a renewed sense
                of purpose. We may not have all the answers yet, but we're moving forward with what we know. And we're
                doing it with you—the African author—in mind.</p>
            <div class="section-title">We created ITAN to solve two major challenges:</div>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Visibility</strong></li>
                <li><strong>Monetization</strong></li>
            </ol>
            <div class="section-title">What ITAN Offers</div>
            <div class="offer-item">
                <strong>1. Multi-format Publishing Tools:</strong><br>
                We begin with eBooks, but will expand to audio and print formats—so your stories can reach readers in
                every way possible.
            </div>
            <div class="offer-item">
                <strong>2. Monthly Analytics:</strong><br>
                Gain insight into how your book is performing through your personalized analytics dashboard. We offer
                author dashboard with real-time sales, downloads, and earnings.
            </div>
            <div class="offer-item">
                <strong>3. AI-Driven Discoverability & Global Marketing:</strong><br>
                Through advanced algorithms and aggressive digital campaigns, we'll get your books in front of the right
                readers—those who appreciate and are willing to pay for your stories.
            </div>
            <div class="offer-item">
                <strong>4. Platform Improvements:</strong><br>
                Our platform is constantly evolving, as we update with new features to ensure ITAN remains the leading
                choice for Afrocentric publishing. Upcoming features include multilingual translation tools, hardcopy
                printing, audio translation and more.
            </div>
            <div class="offer-item">
                <strong>5. International Collaborations:</strong><br>
                We will build international distribution via Lulu, Ingram Spark, bookshop.org, Smashwords, etc. while
                maintaining the IGP brand.
            </div>
            <div class="offer-item">
                <strong>6. Author Community:</strong><br>
                Create an ITAN Author Academy and community that offers free courses and workshops on writing,
                self-editing, and book promotion.
            </div>
            <div class="section-title">How You Can Help Us Succeed</div>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Invite Other Authors:</strong> Like a thriving market, the more books on our platform, the
                more readers we attract. Help us build a vibrant ecosystem by inviting fellow writers. A link is
                given to every author in the dashboard to invite other writers. Please invite other writers.</li>
                <li><strong>Publish Quality Work:</strong> Ensure your manuscript is well-edited and professionally
                formatted. Great stories deserve great presentation— hire a skilled editor, design a compelling
                cover, and craft a story so irresistible your readers can't stop talking about it.</li>
                <li><strong>Stay Informed:</strong> We'll periodically send you resources and training invites. Read
                them—they're designed to help you grow and sell more books.</li>
                <li><strong>Maintain Integrity:</strong> ITAN is committed to building a trustworthy and reputable
                Afrocentric brand. We do not accept plagiarized or AI-generated books. We want human stories—filled
                with soul, emotion, and authenticity. In an era overwhelmed by AI content, real voices matter more
                than ever.</li>
                <li><strong>Promote Your Book:</strong> Don't stop at uploading. Share your book link, talk about it on
                social media, and engage your audience. We'll promote on our end, but your personal efforts make all
                the difference.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="signature">
                <p>Together, we will change the narrative for African literature.<br>
                You create the masterpieces.<br>
                We'll take your stories to the world.</p>
                <p><strong>To you, African Author.<br>
                    To ITAN.<br>
                    To Africa.</strong></p>
                <p>Warm regards,<br>
                <strong>ITAN Technologies LTD</strong>
                </p>
            </div>
